Here are both approaches, starting from your `ProductListPage` tap handler.

## 1. Route Registration (AppShell.xaml.cs)

```csharp
public partial class AppShell : Shell
{
    public AppShell()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
    }
}
```

## 2. Navigating from ProductListPage

```csharp
// --- Approach A: string ID via query string ---
async void OnProductSelected(Product product)
{
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");
}

// --- Approach B: full object via ShellNavigationQueryParameters ---
async void OnProductSelected(Product product)
{
    var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
    {
        { "product", product }
    };
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
}
```

## 3. Receiving Data — ProductDetailsViewModel

```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _productId;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Product _product;

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A: string parameter from query string
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service using the ID
        }

        // Approach B: full object from ShellNavigationQueryParameters
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- **Approach A** — simple string via the URI; good for deep-linkable, serializable IDs. Values arrive as `object` — call `.ToString()`.
- **Approach B** — `ShellNavigationQueryParameters` passes the live object in-memory; no serialization. Use when you already have the object and want to avoid a second lookup.
- Both arrive in the same `ApplyQueryAttributes` dictionary, so you can support either or both in one ViewModel.
- Always `await` `GoToAsync` to avoid race conditions.
